subSubSection.paragraph:
Dorsum (
Figs. 24–25
): Dorsal scutum almost rectangular. Anterior margin with shallow cheliceral sockets and 4 small denticles on each lateral side (
Fig. 24
). Carapace finely granulated. Rougher granules concentrated in the medial region. Some small granules occur in front of each eye mound. Eye mounds with small granules, located near sulcus I and projected laterally (
Fig. 24
). Lateral margins with one row of slightly sharp tubercles. These tubercles are larger toward the distal end of the lateral margin. Mesotergal areas well defined and roughly granulated. Area I divided into left and right halves and constricted by a brief and narrow medial groove (
Fig. 24
). On each half, a lateral small tubercle is evident. Area III with a paramedian pair of low tubercles. Area IV with a paramedian pair of large pointed tubercles (
Fig. 25
). Posterior margin and free tergites with a row of transverse tubercles. Free tergites I–II with slightly larger paramedian tubercles; free tergite II with a paramedian pair of smaller tubercles between the larger pair. Free tergite III with a paramedian pair of strong tubercles, with the same size as those tubercles present on Area IV (
Fig. 25
). Anal operculum roughly granulated.
